Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
placeBondPad(25.10)                                        placeBondPad(25.10)

Name
       placeBondPad - Places a bond pad on a specified I/O instance

Syntax
       placeBondPad

       [-help]

       {-ioInstName <instName> | -selected}

       [-pad <padName>]

       [-pinName <pinName>]

       [-position {i | m | o}]

       [-fix]

       Places  a  bond pad on a specified I/O instance. It defines the stagger
       position of a specified bump on a single or selected  set  of  I/O  in-
       stances.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each placeBondPad parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man placeBondPad

       -fix   Assigns a fixed status to the specified bond pad.

              This restricts other bond pad commands from modifying  the  bond
              pad.

       -ioInstName <name>
              Specifies  the  name  of  the I/O instance of where the bond pad
              will be placed.

       -pad <padName>
              Specifies the name of the bond pad.

       -pinName <pinName>
              Specifies the name of the pin inside the instance.

       -position {I | M | O}
              Defines the stagger position of the specified bond  pad  on  the
              specified I/O instance. You can stagger the position of the bond
              pad using the inner (I), middle (M), and outer (O) positions.

       -selected
              Places  a  selected  bond pad on the specified I/O instance. You
              must first select the bond pad in the design display area,  then
              use  this  parameter  to place the bond pad on the specified I/O
              instance.

Related Information
              * checkBondPadSpacing

              * fixBondPad

              * getBondPad

              * spaceBondPad

              * staggerBondPad

              * unfixBondPad

